# Steps to install SASS (simulated for GitHub-only workflow)

1. Normally, we install Node.js (version 20.16.0) using NVM:
   curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash

2. Reopen terminal and run:
   nvm install 20.16.0

3. Then, we install SASS using npm:
   npm install sass -v 1.63.4

Since I'm using GitHub online only, these steps are noted for documentation.
